1. Price is negotiable, within reason. (i.e. if you message me saying 800 dollars plus food stamps and/or any sort of derelict vehicle you will be 1. ignored 2. heckled)

1. 5.45 Ammo is seriously cheap, and I'm throwing in some free rounds (not the bad kind either, the zinc Silver Bear ammo.

3. Comes with a ~370 dollar scope (Leupold 3x9)
4. These mags are very hard to come by and the gun comes with 3.

This is the Marlin 57M that was built from 1959 to 1969 in .22 magnum and features a 24" microgroove barrel which is tube fed that holds 15 rounds with a very smooth action. With a tube magazine holding 15 rounds and the lever that only moves 1.25" to completely cycle the rifle, you can really put bullets on target in very short order. The scope is mounted high rings so you can use iron sights for targets at 25 to 50 yards. Marlin did not build any of the Model 57 rifles with a serial number so this rifle has no serial number.  This lever action rifle is in wonderful condition and is quite rare.  It marks the 100 years of Marlin in 1970.  

I am asking $625 for this rare rifle and will include 50 rounds of CCI Maxi-Mags at my asking price. Any price negations will result in the ammunition being taken out of the deal to start.
